Race.SpecificTitle: Incorporation of St. George -- Incorporation - Gov.
Race.FullText: Shall the City of St. George be incorporated?

Race.SpecificTitle: Goodwood Homesites Cr. Prev. and Nbrhd. Imp. Dist. -- $150/$450/$70 Parcel Fee Continuation - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Goodwood Homesites Crime Prevention and
Neighborhood Improvement District Proposition
Race.FullText: Shall Goodwood Homesites Crime Prevention and Neighborhood Improvement District ("District"), be authorized to continue to levy and collect an annual parcel fee on each improved parcel located within the District for ten years beginning in 2020 and ending in 2029 as previously levied in an amount not to exceed one hundred fifty dollars ($150.00) for residential parcels, four hundred and fifty dollars ($450.00) for commercial parcels and seventy dollars ($70.00) for parcels qualifying for a special assessment level of ad valorem taxes pursuant to Article VII, Section 18(G)(1) of the Louisiana Constitution and to exercise the option to adjust the fee annually provided said fee does not exceed two hundred dollars ($200.00) for residential parcels, five hundred dollars ($500.00) for commercial parcels and ninety dollars ($90.00) for parcels qualifying for special assessment with the proceeds of the fee (after deducting administrative costs) to be used for the purposes of aiding in crime prevention, adding to the security of district residents, and providing beautification and overall improvement to the District pursuant to La. R.S. 33:9097.20 and 9099.1 ($56,200 is reasonably estimated to be collected from the initial levy)?
